Diagnosis.
Postpedicel brownish black with a yellow spot on distal ventral half (
Fig. 60
); thorax brown pruinose with two longitudinal greyish yellow stripes extending from base of postpronotal lobe to the posterior margin of mesonotum (
Fig. 64
); epandrium digitiform turned inward (
Figs. 65–70
).
